      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics FEA with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity; model form justified by published literature for Ti-6Al-4V implant components under quasi-static loading.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive model selected based on published tensile characterisation of medical-grade Ti-6Al-4V (ASTM F136). Sensitivity study with three hardening parameterisations (BISO, multilinear isotropic, Chaboche) shows <3% QoI variation. Model form uncertainty bounded and acceptable for the COU."
    },
