      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). All specimens drawn from the same production lot with full material traceability. Dimensional inspection confirms specimens within drawing tolerance. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASTM E2935."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate clinical loading envelope; multiple load levels or configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 specifies a single compression-bending configuration at a standardised offset distance. Only one test condition (axial compression at 10 mm anterior offset) was evaluated, which does not span the full clinical loading envelope (e.g., lateral bending, torsion not included). This factor is below the required level; the shortfall is acknowledged and bounded by the scope limitation of the COU to F1717 compression-bending only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to test fixture constraints; loading rate and environmental conditions matched.",
      "rationale": "Test fixture geometry digitised and replicated in FEA boundary conditions. Displacement-controlled loading rate (5 mm/min) confirmed quasi-static; inertial effects negligible (kinetic energy <0.1% strain energy). Ambient temperature testing matched to FEA isothermal assumption. Potting depth and screw insertion torque recorded and replicated in FEA preload."
    },
