      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Maximum E/uval = 1.41 (stiffness, Lab B). All three QoIs pass the 1.96 threshold. Percent differences also within 10% bound. Visual comparison of force-displacement curves shows good agreement in both elastic and early post-yield regions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly relate to construct fatigue life prediction inputs and clinical failure modes (screw fracture, rod fracture). QoI relevance is high."
    },
